=========================================
Major repo-wide problems are listed here.
=========================================

The changes made by 02add_lib_dir.sh, 03swap_search_dirs.sh only affect options
passed to intermediate builds of gcc during bootstrap, so that can work, but
don't affect runtime defaults used by gcc when no args given.

A change which fixes the builtin include directories has now been applied to
all the 3.2 releases, and the 4.9 releases will follow shortly.

The 3.2 releases can now automatically find the correct target crt*.o objects
provided by the target system.  They also have a backported fix from 2007 which
causes the newly built crtend.o and crtendS.o to have no entries in .eh_frame
section, which finally cuts out the vast bulk of the `make check-gcc` errors.

-----

Using the configure options in configure-opts, building and installing the
kludged gcc 3.2.3 works in a single make invocation e.g. make bootstrap
install.  make bootstrap then a separate make install tries to rebuild cc1,
and gets it wrong.

This might just be me not using gcc's configure and make right, but vanilla
(non-kludged) 6.3.0 doesn't have this problem.

